Create a low-fidelity mobile app wireframe for an Online Learning Platform called "LearnHub".

Design 5 mobile screens in grayscale wireframe style (black, white, and grey only). Use simple rectangles, placeholders, and text labels. Do not use colors, images, or detailed UI elements.

Screen 1: Login Screen
- App Logo placeholder
- Welcome Back heading
- Email input field
- Password input field
- Login button
- Forgot Password link
- Sign Up option

Screen 2: Home Screen
- Search bar
- Course Categories section
- Featured Courses section
- Navigation bar at bottom

Screen 3: Course Details Screen
- Course image placeholder
- Course title
- Course description
- Course duration
- Enroll Now button

Screen 4: My Courses Screen
- List of enrolled courses
- Progress bars for each course
- Continue Learning button

Screen 5: Profile Screen
- Profile picture placeholder
- Student name
- Email address
- Settings option
- Help & Support option
- Logout button

Arrange all 5 screens side by side in a clean and professional wireframe layout suitable for a UI/UX internship submission.
